    "summary": "As humans, we have one of the most complex interacting ways in the whole animal kingdom. This does not make us special, but it creates a sensitive mind-balance in between pragmatism and idealism and yet realism and irrationality. \nThese balances need to be always kept in mind, to avoid exceeding in one or the other direction. This also means avoiding time-loss on the wrong path, overthinking about details, or running too fast for the result.\n \nI am Sarah, and I am a Communication and a Digital Strategist. I try to apply this view both, in the Marketing field, and in the way I manage work among colleagues. The key to success is to find the best way not only to communicate to the world outside: respecting the logic, and the illogic, that drive our minds; but also, find the best way to work together as a team. Ideas are driven together, to keep a natural communication and yet create a well-analyzed marketing strategy. \n\nWhat about my life outside work? I am a swimmer, I love gardening, a passion that I discovered during the time of Corona, and I am exceptionally curious. I like to read and document myself on thousands of topics that I would struggle to list, as well as to discover new activities like new sports or crocheting. Yes, I go from black to white just basing on what catches my heart. I still love climbing for instance, even if I am really bad at it!\n \nJoin me here on LinkedIn and let\u2019s create a connection.",
