            "title": "Comfort Sense Project - University of Turin",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 2,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2015
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 11,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                }
            },
            "description": "Description from the official website: ComfortSense is a project funded by the Piedmont Region under the \"Internet of Data\" program. The goal of the project is to obtain information about the comfort of users in a particular context; this information is collected and sent to a central system directly from the people who daily live in that particular environment and then, be cross-referenced with data from environmental sensors. With this method it is possible to understand the relevant variables related to the use of places, with two main aims: on one hand, to promote a more sustainable buildings management and, on the other hand, to direct users' actions towards energy saving through an increase in awareness derived from the information collected.\n\nThe context selected for the experimentation foreseen by the project is the Luigi Einaudi Campus (CLE) and the subjects which have been involved in this experimentation are students, teachers, and employees who attend and work in the structure. The Lab is maintained by UniTo professors, researchers, and user experience design experts. During the Lab, broader issues were also addressed, such as the theme of big data, energy network science, smart cities design.\nThe meetings represented the main phases of participatory design and, therefore, were divided as follows:\n\n1) Introduction to the living lab and basic concepts.\n2) Collection of needs of CLE users, through interviews and observation\n3) Brainstorming for the definition of the concept, storyboard, and scenarios\n4) Ideation phase of the identified solutions\n5) Definition of the functionality of the device\n6) Definition of interaction modes\n7) Introduction to the theme of the Internet of Things and relations with energy networks\n8) Introduction to the theme of big data\n9) Introduction to the design of the smart and sustainable city",
